comments.message:
instead of reading "busType" from json and appending here, we can make it as simple-

string deleteDeviceCmd = "echo " + deviceAddress + " > /sys/bus/i2c/devices/i2c-" + busNum + "/delete_device";

executeCmd(deleteDeviceCmd);

instead of reading "busType" and driverType from json and appending here(which we are going to omit in future), we can make it as simple-

string newDeviceCmd = "echo 24c32 " + deviceAddress + " > /sys/bus/i2c/devices/i2c-" + busNum + "/new_device";

executeCmd(newDeviceCmd );

I am handling delete/new device also as part of createBindUnbindDriverCmnd(), that will make it more simpler.

once you will fix this merge conflict, you will have 
createBindUnbindDriverCmnd in util.hpp.

please make use of it as-

300    executeCmd(createBindUnbindDriverCmnd(deviceAddress, busType, driverType, "unbind"));
301    executeCmd(createBindUnbindDriverCmnd(deviceAddress, busType, driverType, "bind"));

I am working on a commit where I am making createBindUnbindDriverCmnd more independent i.e. independent of busType, driverType.
So need to send only 2 params in future-
createBindUnbindDriverCmnd(YOUR_UNIQUE_DEV_ADDR, YOUR_ACTION);
